12
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:07,880
辣身舞 2
情迷哈瓦那
根据真实故事改编

13
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,820
不管是摔门还是以沉默来抗议
Slamming doors and giving the silent treatment...

14
00:01:10,870 --> 00:01:12,300
也改变不了他们的决定
couldn't change that...

15
00:01:12,330 --> 00:01:14,890
但这比承认我害怕容易得多
but it was easier than admitting I was really scared.

16
00:01:14,940 --> 00:01:16,730
但至少我家人都很高兴
At least everyone else was happy.

17
00:01:16,770 --> 00:01:18,900
父亲在福德公司高升了
Dad got his big promotion from Ford.

18
00:01:18,940 --> 00:01:21,410
母亲可以风风光地旅行了 而苏西
Mom got to travel in style,and Susie...

19
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:25,210
她就算在飓风中也能泰然自若
I swear that girl could adjust in a hurricane.

20
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:30,770
欢迎来到海洋酒店
Welcome to the Hotel Oceana.

21
00:02:54,070 --> 00:02:56,260
还不错 对吧
Not too shabby, huh?

22
00:02:57,970 --> 00:02:59,560
这就是我所了解的古巴…
Here's what I know about Cuba...

23
00:02:59,610 --> 00:03:02,130
我高中学的法语派不上用场
my high-school French wasn't going to help me.

24
00:03:02,180 --> 00:03:03,970
一个人都不认识
I didn't know a single person...

25
00:03:04,010 --> 00:03:05,670
虽然没人会谈及这个
and though no one would talk about it...

26
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:08,240
[菲德尔·卡斯特罗：古巴前领导人 推翻了巴蒂斯坦亲美独裁政权]
但菲德尔·卡斯特罗正在领导革命
Fidel Castro was leading a people in a revolution...

27
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:10,410
[巴蒂斯塔·伊·萨尔迪瓦：古巴总统 亲美独裁者]
对抗巴蒂斯塔总统
against President Batista...

28
00:03:10,450 --> 00:03:13,650
至少这里你不会听到这种事
not that you would know it from this place.

29
00:03:16,660 --> 00:03:19,630
这就是古巴 没人管你做什么
This is Cuba. Nobody cares what you do here.

30
00:03:19,660 --> 00:03:21,150
苏西 抽烟吗
Susie, you want a smoke?

31
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,760
小心这小姐 她会带坏你
Watch out for this one.She's a bad influence.

32
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,490
我当你在夸我好了
I'll take that as a compliment.

33
00:03:25,530 --> 00:03:28,260
她很快就会唆使你逃课了
She'll have you ditching classes in no time.

34
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:30,030
如果我没记错 某人
As I recall,there's a certain someone...

35
00:03:30,070 --> 00:03:31,630
喜欢和我一起逃课
that likes to ditch them with me.

36
00:03:33,070 --> 00:03:35,840
别忘了报名参加曼波舞课
Don't forget to sign up for mambo lessons.

37
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:38,040
每天都有课程
Mambo classes are held every day...

38
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:40,980
[琼·克莉佛：电视剧《反斗小宝贝》里一个完美主妇的母亲 完美榜样的代名词]
我的天啊 琼·克莉佛来哈瓦那了
My God. June Cleaver is in Havana.

39
00:03:42,380 --> 00:03:46,110
事实上 那是我姐姐凯蒂 她很聪明
Actually, that's my sister Katey. She's a real brain.

40
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,850
噢 真的吗
Oh, really?

41
00:03:47,890 --> 00:03:50,050
可不 她可能会考上拉德克利夫学院
Yeah. She's probably going to Radcliffe.

42
00:03:50,090 --> 00:03:51,850
哦？主修时装吗
What, majoring in fashion?

43
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:58,560
过来和我们一起吧 这里有位置
Why don't you join us? There's room here.

44
00:04:04,940 --> 00:04:06,500
我是詹姆斯·菲尔普斯
I'm James Phelps.

45
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:07,870
嗨 我是凯蒂·米勒
Hi. Katey Miller.

46
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:09,210
很高兴认识你
Pleasure to meet you.

47
00:04:10,450 --> 00:04:11,740
- 你是不是…  - 是的
- Are you the...  - Yeah.

48
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:14,980
- 你父亲在我父亲手下工作  - 是的
- Your dad works for my dad.  - Yeah.

49
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:18,850
这是希拉 伊芙 波莉 还有史蒂夫
This is Sheila, Eve, Polly, and Steph...

50
00:04:18,890 --> 00:04:20,750
你认识苏西 对吧
and I guess you know Susie,right?

51
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:23,750
你真要去拉德克利夫学院读书吗
So, are you really going to Radcliffe?

52
00:04:23,790 --> 00:04:25,220
到春天才能知道
I won't know till spring.

53
00:04:25,260 --> 00:04:27,750
哇 姑娘们 注意啦
Whoa. Watch out, girls.

54
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,490
如果你满脑袋都是课本的话
I guess if your head's in your books...

55
00:04:29,530 --> 00:04:30,660
你应该没有时间
you really don't have time...

56
00:04:30,700 --> 00:04:34,570
去考虑天气这种傻事了
to think about silly things like the weather.

57
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,860
很冷么
Chilly?

58
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:38,600
噢
Oh.

59
00:04:40,010 --> 00:04:42,880
真对不起 是我的错
I'm so sorry. It's my fault.

60
00:04:42,910 --> 00:04:45,670
别弄了 去给我拿一杯新的
No, just go get new drinks.

61
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,610
愚蠢的拉美佬
Stupid spic.

62
00:04:56,460 --> 00:04:58,150
失陪了
Excuse me.

63
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:06,800
- 你要加班赔这些饮料  - 可错不在我
- Tú sabes que trabajas que pagar por eso.  - Oye que no fuera mi culpa.

64
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,800
工作时给我小心点
Trabajas con cuidado.

65
00:05:07,970 --> 00:05:08,890
先生 打扰了
Excuse me. Senor?

66
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:10,440
有什么能为您效劳的 小姐？
How may I help you, senorita?

67
00:05:10,470 --> 00:05:12,800
我撞倒了那些饮料 我想赔偿
I knocked into those drinks. I'd like to pay for them.

68
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:16,440
没这个必要 只是个意外 失陪了
That will not be necessary. Accidents happen. Excuse me.

69
00:05:20,740 --> 00:05:21,350
对不起…
Yo tengo siento...

70
00:05:21,350 --> 00:05:22,600
我会讲英语
I speak English...

71
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:26,650
我不需要你的施舍
and I don't need your charity.

72
00:05:26,690 --> 00:05:29,120
我不是这个意思
It's not.

73
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:31,130
别担心 这没什么
Don't worry about it. It's OK.

74
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:35,160
我很抱歉 她那样叫你
I'm sorry for what she called you.

75
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:37,060
- 这没什么  - 我不这么觉得
- That was nothing.  - Not to me.

76
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:39,230
那为什么要由你来道歉？
Then why are you apologizing?

77
00:05:47,610 --> 00:05:49,370
你们舞跳得真好
You guys were so good.

78
00:05:49,410 --> 00:05:50,340
你妈妈很出色
Your mother was good.

79
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:54,440
我就一般般
I was OK.

80
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,420
- 爸爸？ - 嗯
- Dad?  - Hmm.

81
00:05:56,450 --> 00:05:57,890
我很抱歉
I'm sorry

82
00:05:57,890 --> 00:06:01,860
我一直对来古巴兴致不高
I haven't been excited about all of this.

83
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:05,960
宝贝 没事的
Sweetheart, it's OK.

84
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:10,230
高三把你从学校拖出来确实很糟糕
Senior year is a terrible time to drag you out of school...

85
00:06:10,260 --> 00:06:11,990
况且你是班级之星啊
especially when you're the star of the class.

86
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:14,260
- 爸  - 嘿 别否认
- Dad.  - Come on. Don't deny it.

87
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:16,130
你应该感到骄傲
Be proud of it.

88
00:06:16,170 --> 00:06:19,570
你在这里也会很出色的
You'll do great here, too.

89
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:36,320
我不能站在您的脚上跳舞了
I can't stand on your feet anymore.

90
00:06:42,260 --> 00:06:44,600
- 嘿 你还记得这个  - 是啊
- Hey, you remembered that.  - Yeah.

91
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,990
非常好
Very good.

92
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:52,810
让我们继续上节课所学的内容
Let's continue where we left off.

93
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:55,900
拿出十八号课本 打开二十五页
Book 18, page 25.

94
00:06:55,940 --> 00:06:58,340
凯蒂 尽力去跟上进度 行吗
Katey, just do your best to follow, all right?

95
00:06:58,380 --> 00:07:00,370
没问题 这我去年就读过了
It's OK. I read it last year.

96
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:03,510
你们安静
Knock it off.

97
00:07:03,550 --> 00:07:06,680
那你从第三百四十二行开始读吧
Well, then perhaps you'd like to begin reading at line 342.

98
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:11,790
此时求婚者开始载歌载舞
"Now the suitors turned to dance and song...

99
00:07:11,830 --> 00:07:13,920
随着欢快的节拍摇摆
"to the lovely beaten sway...

100
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:17,490
等待着黄昏的到来
"waiting for dusk to come upon them there...

101
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:21,970
[出自《奥德赛》第18卷]
“夜幕降临 他们沉湎在欢悦之中”
and the dark night came upon them, lost in pleasure."

102
00:07:25,110 --> 00:07:27,170
有没有人能告诉我们
Can anyone tell us...

103
00:07:27,210 --> 00:07:30,370
这段话怎么理解？
the significance of this passage?

104
00:07:30,410 --> 00:07:32,900
就是一群醉汉在胡闹咯
It's a bunch of drunk guys doing it.

105
00:07:37,690 --> 00:07:38,600
雅典娜
Athena

106
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:42,850
希望求婚者们继续侵扰奥德修斯的住处
wants the suitors to keep invading Odysseus' house...

107
00:07:42,890 --> 00:07:45,290
这样他就会怒杀所有求婚者
so that he'll get angry enough to kill them.

108
00:07:45,330 --> 00:07:47,320
那女神为什么要这么做？
And why does the goddess want that?

109
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:53,860
她希望奥德修斯发掘自己的力量
She wants Odysseus to find his strength...

110
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,560
和勇气？
and courage?

111
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,930
非常好
Very good.

112
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,480
需要我载你回家吗
Need a ride home?

113
00:08:17,730 --> 00:08:21,960
不用了 我可以的 我有很多功课要补
No. I'm OK. I got a lot of catching up to do.

114
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,120
其实 许多女孩子
You know, a lot of girls...

115
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,560
不会显露出她们的聪明才智
don't like to let on when they're smart.

116
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,120
我知道 我不该…
I know.I shouldn't have said...

117
00:08:26,170 --> 00:08:28,500
不 不 我喜欢
No. No, I like that.

118
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:30,770
我喜欢那样的你
I like that about you.

119
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:38,540
星期六晚上我几个朋友要去乡村俱乐部
A bunch of us are going to our country club on Saturday night.

120
00:08:38,580 --> 00:08:42,310
有乐队表演 音乐很酷
There'll be a band.The music's pretty cool.

121
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:45,780
你愿意和我一起去吗
Would you like to go with me?

122
00:08:45,820 --> 00:08:49,260
我真的有很多功课要做
I really do have a lot of work to do.

123
00:08:49,290 --> 00:08:50,520
在星期六的晚上？
On a Saturday night?

124
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:53,320
哇哦
Wow.

125
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:57,420
来嘛 我相信就算荷马
Come on. I'm sure even Homer took some time off...

126
00:08:57,470 --> 00:08:59,560
在写伊利亚特和奥德赛之间 也有空闲的
between The lliad and The Odyssey.

127
00:09:01,140 --> 00:09:03,540
那 好吧
Well, sure. OK.

128
00:09:03,570 --> 00:09:05,840
好
OK.

129
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,570
我们都到齐了 可以开车了
We're all here now. You can go.

130
00:09:40,210 --> 00:09:41,400
美女
Bonita.

131
00:10:52,450 --> 00:10:53,440
就这样
Eso.

132
00:11:06,260 --> 00:11:08,630
你突然受到古巴音乐的鼓动吗
You felt the sudden urge for Cuban music?

133
00:11:08,660 --> 00:11:11,060
我没赶上校车
The van left without me.

134
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:12,430
已经走了一个小时了
I've been walking for an hour.

135
00:11:12,470 --> 00:11:13,760
我可以送你回家
I can walk you back.

136
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,390
哦 不 你不必送我
Oh, no. You don't have to do that.

137
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,270
是的 没错
Oh, yeah, you're right.

138
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,140
你早晚能自己找到路的
You'll find your way sooner or later.

139
00:11:19,170 --> 00:11:21,900
说不定一周或一个月就找到了
Maybe in a week or a month.

140
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:23,970
我去道个别
Let me just say good-bye.

141
00:11:24,010 --> 00:11:26,210
爷爷！
Abuelito!

142
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,210
真棒
Bueno.

143
00:11:37,060 --> 00:11:38,030
你叫他什么？
What was it you called him?

144
00:11:38,060 --> 00:11:41,520
Abuelito 就是我爷爷
Abuelito. It's my grandpa.

145
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,990
我是凯蒂 你的名字是？
I'm Katey. What's your name?

146
00:11:45,030 --> 00:11:46,930
哈维尔
Javier.

147
00:11:46,970 --> 00:11:51,060
这么说 你认识五个西语单词了吗
So what, you know like five words in Spanish?

148
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:53,270
可能有十个呢
Maybe ten.

149
00:11:53,310 --> 00:11:55,500
你为什么那么努力学习
And what are you studying so hard to do?

150
00:11:55,540 --> 00:11:57,570
我也不知道
I haven't figured it out yet.

151
00:11:57,610 --> 00:12:00,140
来 我帮你拿
Here. Let me take that.

152
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:07,840
我从没见过那样的舞蹈
I've never seen dancing like that.

153
00:12:07,890 --> 00:12:09,320
什么样的舞蹈？
Like what?

154
00:12:09,360 --> 00:12:12,260
我说不清
I don't know.

155
00:12:12,290 --> 00:12:14,990
我很喜欢 它非常地
I like it. It's very...

156
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,630
- 非常古巴？ - 没错
- Very Cuban?  - Yeah.

157
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:52,300
- 我们应该离开这里  - 为什么
- We should get off the street.  - Why?

158
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:54,260
你不明白他们在唱什么
You don't understand what they're singing.

159
00:13:00,270 --> 00:13:02,440
不！
No!

160
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:03,670
不！
No!

161
00:13:03,710 --> 00:13:05,940
往那边跑！
That way!

162
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:10,310
所以你得… 没事 她回来了
So you've got... OK. Here she comes.

163
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:12,220
非常感谢您
Thank you so much.

164
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:16,350
感谢上帝 凯蒂 你去哪儿了
Thank God. Katey, where have you been?

165
00:13:16,390 --> 00:13:18,520
我错过了校车
I missed the bus.

166
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:20,030
我没事 走回来的
I'm fine. I walked.

167
00:13:20,060 --> 00:13:22,890
天啊 凯蒂 为什么不给我打电话
For heaven's sakes.Katey, why didn't you call me?

168
00:13:22,930 --> 00:13:25,920
我担心你被叛乱分子绑架了
For all I knew, you could have been kidnapped by rebels.

169
00:13:25,970 --> 00:13:28,870
你该担心的不是叛乱分子
It's not the rebels you should be worried about.

170
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:30,130
你说什么？
What did you say?

171
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:38,070
你说得对 我错了 我应该打给你的
You're right. I'm sorry. I should have called.

172
00:13:38,110 --> 00:13:39,410
亲爱的 你的书包呢
Honey, where's your book bag?

173
00:13:43,020 --> 00:13:45,250
我把它留在学校了
I left it at school.

174
00:13:45,290 --> 00:13:46,410
太重了
It was heavy.

175
00:14:37,070 --> 00:14:38,770
哦 天啊
Oh, God.

176
00:14:38,810 --> 00:14:42,040
多亏这些无聊的美国书
